    • getOrCreateDynamicAssignmentState

      public static DynamicAssignmentState getOrCreateDynamicAssignmentState(KeyableBean entity, Group group)
      Generate a fingerprint based on the supplied entity's properties and use the result to retrieve a DynamicAssignmentState
      Parameters:
      entity - The entity whose properties will be used to generate the fingerprint
      group - May be null. If non-null, will be used in the fingerprint as well, so that per-group DynamicAssignmentStates may be maintained
      Returns:
      A DynamicAssignmentState with the resulting fingerprint value

    • findAssignment

      @InternalAPI @Deprecated public static Key findAssignment(com.guidewire.pl.domain.assignment.RoundRobinState state, Set<Key> assigneesToChooseFrom, AssignmentType type, KeyableBean assignableOwner)
      Deprecated.
      Subclasser utility; does the actual work of finding an assignment by stepping through a list of potential assignees and checking their load factors.
      Parameters:
      state - describes the potential assignees and their load factors
      assigneesToChooseFrom - if non-null, the subset of assignee ids that can be selected. Used by assignByUserAttributes to find the "most available" of a set of users that match a given set of attributes.
      type - the type of assignment
      assignableOwner -
      Returns:
      the key of the assignee that should be given the item, or null if no eligible assignee exist
